4. sw.js (Final)

The Service Worker ensures that once the user visits the page, the application stays available even if the network is disconnected.
JavaScript

const CACHE_NAME = 'video-editor-v1';
self.addEventListener('fetch', event => {
  event.respondWith(
    caches.match(event.request).then(response => response || fetch(event.request))
  );
});

To complete this, simply ensure you have your assets/ folder populated with your icon files. Once you host these files on a secure HTTPS server (or use npx serve), your browser will automatically detect the manifest.json and offer to install the application to your OS.
